 parsing of the return xml or json to retrieve the correct query key or webenv string needed to pass to efetch.  (Perhaps there's a way to get it to return just that?)  Also, it currently can create a history file and a file of IDs, but they're the same file.\n\nI could finish this one part to be able to accomplish my immediate goal, but changes would be needed in biopython as well, and it appears that these things are just the tip of the iceberg.","files":null}]}